                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d237">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72119/1834</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Switzerland</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_SPA1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stovall</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-08-13T13:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 13, 1918, 1 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2437. Your confidential mail despatch 3788.<note n="1" xml:id="d237fn1">Not
                        printed; see the Minister’s telegram No. 3884 of July 5, <hi rend="italic"
                            >ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_276">p. 276</ref>.</note> Advise
                        <persName>Herron</persName> that he may say substantially to <persName>De
                        Fiori</persName> that he (<persName>Herron</persName>) has so distinctly
                    gained the impression that the Government at Washington objects to indirect
                    approaches of this kind and is definitely determined to entertain only official
                    suggestions coming from accredited representatives of a government, that he has
                    come to the conclusion that it would prejudice matters rather than promote them
                    to seek to ascertain the attitude of our government in the way that <persName>De
                        Fiori</persName> has hoped that he (<persName>Herron</persName>) might be
                    willing to attempt to ascertain it.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
